<br>
For two days now, I've been in small talks with Verant. As you know, they are very hush hush to releasing any kind of info that they are working on. However, I did learn that there are some wizard improvements in the works - something to do with usefulness (especially to groups) in Velious that is not damage related. They won't release the complete info to me until after the E3 Convention in Los Angeles. I will keep you all updated with what I can find out. Also, I did make sure that this had nothing to do with Translocates or the portal to Luclin. <br>
<br>
I would like you to notice it says: Usefulness in VELIOUS. I guess Velious is the only continent in the game now? None of us ever go to Kunark to fight. Nah. Are they just stupid or do they have a problem with wizards being up to par with other players. Doing 663 dmg to a 300k mob at lvl 55.... wow thats power.... Get a clue Verant.<br>
<br>
The real fix is increased damage/haste (mainly damage). Thats it. We dont even need mana regen. And you have to love these great bitch...I mean translocate spells LOL. THANK GOD FOR /anon!!! Also harvest needs a looking at. I get a half a bubble of mana per 10 min wait. Wow thats impressive.. enough to cast one spell.<br>
<br>
Eelienu Lightbringer<br>
